9999999997px;"><strong>No
Heroes Here</strong></h3>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<table width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" role=
=3D"presentation" style=3D"mso-table-lspace:0pt;mso-table-rspace:0pt;word-b=
reak:break-word;"><tbody><tr><td style=3D"padding-bottom:32px;"><div style=
=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;Inter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;=
;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;line-height:150%;text-al=
ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;">It=E2=80=99s been suggested that McGrath can make Louis Vuitton a major=
 player in designer
makeup=E2=80=94a space that McGrath, in fact, helped create. She was integr=
al in the creation of Armani=E2=80=99s Luminous Silk foundation (2000) and =
Dior=E2=80=99s Diorshow mascara (2002), two of the most iconic makeup produ=
cts ever created, both rare examples of products that <em>still</em> power =
their respective businesses. But as an industry executive recently noted, d=
espite a surplus of launches, there have been no <em>real </em>hits outside=
 of the existing players and their hero products.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;
margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">They=
 have a point. Armani Beauty, Dior, and Chanel comprise a reliable trio of =
mainstays in designer makeup. Beyond them, it=E2=80=99s pretty grim: Valent=
ino=E2=80=99s foray into makeup was a giant flop; L=E2=80=99Or=C3=A9al coul=
dn=E2=80=99t make Prada work (=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s too intellectual entire=
ly,=E2=80=9D said a high-level beauty source); and YSL Beauty=E2=80=99s rel=
evancy continues to wane. Givenchy is still trying to dig itself out of the=
 Prisme Libre debacle, and Gucci feels lost
and extremely disjointed, with the makeup still tied to the creative vision=
 of <strong>Alessandro Michele</strong>, who left the brand in 2022. Don=E2=
=80=99t even get me started on Celine, one of the biggest failures to launc=
h since Valentino and Prada went into makeup. (It=E2=80=99s complicated, an=
d explained in part by <strong>Hedi Slimane</strong>=E2=80=99s departure.)<=
/p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;=
margin-bottom:0px;">But does Louis Vuitton actually aspire to compete
with the Big Three? Initially, I thought La Beaut=C3=A9 Louis Vuitton could=
 be a great vehicle to expand LVMH=E2=80=99s designer beauty presence beyon=
d Dior, since an initial launch within Louis Vuitton=E2=80=99s retail netwo=
rk could eventually give way to a larger Sephora rollout. (You don=E2=80=99=
t have to look much further than the 2017 launch of Fenty, another LVMH-own=
ed brand, to know how powerful Sephora=E2=80=99s backing can be.) Unfortuna=
tely, insiders say Sephora is too <em>down-market</em> for Louis Vuitton=E2=
=80=99s makeup,
which, like its fragrance, may only ever be sold in its own stores. =E2=80=
=9CThe positioning was runway=E2=80=93=E2=80=93which is <em>not</em> commer=
cial,=E2=80=9D another insider noted. Still, I=E2=80=99m holding out for so=
me kind of retail partnership, even if it=E2=80=99s with Neiman Marcus and =
Saks.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin:0;">If I had to guess, La Beaut=C3=A9 Louis Vuitton=E2=80=99s introduct=
ion will resemble that of Herm=C3=A8s=E2=80=99s beauty. From the first lips=
ticks that launched in 2020, and even the nail polish,
Herm=C3=A8s=E2=80=99s measured entr=C3=A9e into color cosmetics has been ca=
refully executed. (Five of the colorblocked lipsticks have been neatly disp=
layed in my bathroom for <em>years</em>.) As with Louis Vuitton, Herm=C3=A8=
s is so strong in leather goods that beauty, a tiny piece of their overall =
business, will never be the priority. The benefit for Herm=C3=A8s, as it ma=
y be for La Beaut=C3=A9 Louis Vuitton, is that makeup will never be driven =
by sales goals, or a need to scale at breakneck speed to make numbers or ac=
hieve
global rankings. It just needs to be <em>good</em>.</p></div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
